statement.title: Problem Description
statement.content:
The I-number of x is defined to be an integer y, which satisfied the the conditions below:
1. y>x;
2. the sum of each digit of y(under base 10) is the multiple of 10;
3. among all integers that satisfy the two conditions above, y shouble be the minimum.
Given x, you're required to calculate the I-number of x.

statement.title: Input
statement.content:
An integer T(T��100) will exist in the first line of input, indicating the number of test cases.
The following T lines describe all the queries, each with a positive integer x. The length of x will not exceed 105.

statement.title: Output
statement.content: Output the I-number of x for each query.
